<br>
What annoys me the most is that FV had a trust. Since we were able to keep the sleeper sleeping, we had that 'small' town feel. There was something people could just 'take' but no one did because it would upset everyone else. Now it doesn't have that feel anymore. After the May 8th changes, FV might as well be any other blueby server. I don't think I even care about the FV issues anymore.  We are now the 'tradeabe lewt' server in my eyes.<br>
<br>
By the way, just because you can do something doesn't mean you should. The sleeper is supposed to be the ultimate beast that will destroy the world. Yes, you can wake him. You can also run off a cliff, attack guards at level one, even talk in d00d speak. But if you do, you're not playing the game right. I don't think it's part of Reso's charter to seek out the destruction of Norrath.<br>
<br>
But I'm not mad at Reso, nor anyone else. In a way I'm kinda glad its over. It's not likely I would reach 50 anytime soon, I just don't have the time I used to, so the mask and the tomb are really just a dream any how.<br>
<br>
PS<br>
I can't believe anyone thinks a dorf mask is ANY substitution for a gnome mask. Short and cute vs short and stumpy? <p><html>
