<br>
A lot of people just like to get angry at raiding guilds. It's kind of a fashion. For me, raiding is just grouping but on a bigger scale. Don't see what's wrong with that. Never saw grouping being labelled as &quot;anti roleplay&quot; (except in the case of goods &amp; evils). As for levelling... people who raid actually level slower than the rest of the population. That's partly why the entry requirements for raiding guilds are high. If you joined Resolution at 50, it would be a very, very long time before you hit 60. Believe me, I know. I joined at 15 =P<br>
<br>
A lot of other people get angry because the first lot tell them they should, and because they don't know the whole story (e.g. gnome masks being replaced by dwarf masks, the revamp, primal = prismatic etc).<br>
<br>
Anyway, this is already longer than I'd intended it to be... Summary: mountain out of molehill<br>
